HEADWORD: Meetinghouse
<hw>Meet"ing*house`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A house used
as a place of worship; a church; -- in England, applied only to a house
so used by Dissenters.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

